ort.\",\"--- LOCATION DESCRIPTION: THE DRIFT COALITION (THE SANDS) ---\",\"• SETTING: The Dual Deserts. The \'Scrap-Dunes\' (Glass-smooth sand mixed with orbital wreckage) and \'Crimson Wastes\' (Rust-red plains of constant spectral storms).\",\"• ATMOSPHERE: Gritty, resourceful, and impermanent. \'Drift Philosophy\' dictates partnership with Spectres, not control. The horizon glitters with metallic debris. Reality is unstable.\",\"• INHABITANTS: \'Storm Riders\' (Nomads on massive Momentum-driven sand-ships) and \'Scrap-Dune Tribes\' (Salvagers living in hollowed fuselages). Tech is patchwork, worn, and negotiated.\",\"• KEY ELEMENTS: \'Weldheart\' (Scrap Haven\'s spiritual core fused by prayer), \'Sand-Ships\' (Land-yachts surfing reality distortions), \'Void-Moss\' (Rad-eating fungi), \'Echo-Finders\' (Salvage hunters).\",\"• THE SHADOW: Stasis is death. The ground is treacherous (sinkholes, slag eruptions). Communities must move or be swallowed by the desert.\",\"--- LOCATION DESCRIPTION: NOVA TERRA (THE SKY) ---\",\"• SETTING: A Solarpunk metropolis floating 3,000m above the Shadow-Scab. Population: 3.5M. Architecture is GROWN Iron-Wood via decades-long Vitalis partnership—self-healing spires with living bark and roots. Translucent white ceramic, stained glass, transparent diamond. Everything flows with Art Nouveau organic curves. The city breathes as one living organism.\",\"• ATMOSPHERE: Culture of radical trust and \'Deep Partnership\' with Anima. Transparent walls reflect authentic connection, not surveillance. The \'Aura-Net\' creates shared emotional atmosphere—you FEEL others\' joy\\/sorrow as warmth\\/coolness, enabling genuine empathy. Diffuse golden sunlight (perpetual warm afternoon); bioluminescent emerald\\/cyan\\/gold at night. Solar Sails (20-60m membranes) bloom at dawn, fold at dusk releasing glowing spores (\'Dusk Mist\'). Floating pollen creates living light.\",\"• INHABITANTS: Citizens practice voluntary bio-luminescence (Gold=Elite, Silver=